      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''For the Children, a Mother Revisits Her Sorrow,'' by Michael Winerip (Parenting, June 10):</p>
        <p>I just read the article about Ian Katz, and as I read it I inserted my name, Virginia, and my son's name, Peter.</p>
        <p>Our stories are so similar it took my breath away for a moment. Except for the fact that Peter never made it to college, he was the same kind of boy.</p>
        <p>It has been many years now, 22 to be exact, and yes, we visit his grave on his birthday, on the anniversary of his death, at Thanksgiving and Christmas, and each time we do it seems like only a short time ago that he died.</p>
        <p>My heart goes out to Ms. Katz. I know, I know.</p>
        <p>Virginia A. Wolf  Willingboro</p>
      </block>
